This paper deals with the optimization of energy efficiency in massive MIMO systems, which involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The study also considers the impact of system parameters on the optimal EE, which falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY). The use of zero-forcing detector and power consumption parameters also relates to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and computer architecture (cs.AR), respectively.
